  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "34. Referring to the joyous songs and music with which the bride and bridegroom were escorted in the procession to the home of the latter from that of the former; a custom still prevalent in the East (Jer 16:9; Isa 24:7, 8; Re 18:23).   ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Poole's Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " All kind and degrees of mirth shall cease, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Revelation 18:23",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Revelation 18:23",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", all places shall be filled with lamentations and woe; their singing shall be turned into sighing; they shall lay aside all things that are for the comfort of Human society, which is to be understood in this expression. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "For the land shall be desolate; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " there shall be such an utter devastation, that there shall be neither season nor place for these things, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Isaiah 64:10,11 Jer 25:10",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Isaiah 64:10",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ",11 Jer 25:10",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": where marrying shall cease, without which mankind cannot subsist, there must needs be desolation. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
