  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Thus the Lord will put an end to all joyfulness in life throughout the land: cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hosea 2:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezekiel 26:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The voice of the bridegroom and the bride is a circumlocution for the mirth of marriage festivities; cf. 1 Macc. 9:39. All joy will be dumb, for the land shall become a waste; as the people had been warned, in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 26:31",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 26:33",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", would be the case if they forsook the Lord. ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
